dcterms:creator: M. R. Garey
D. S. Johnson
R. Sethi
dcterms:description: The Job Shop Scheduling Problem (JSSP) is a type of scheduling problem that aims to determine the optimal sequential assignments of machines to multiple jobs consisting of series of operations while preserving the problem constraints.
dcterms:title: Job Shop Scheduling Problem (JSSP)

dcterms:creator: D. Applegate
W. Cook
dcterms:description: ORB instances are a set of job shop scheduling problems used for computational studies, specifically designed to challenge scheduling algorithms.
dcterms:title: ORB instances

dcterms:creator: J. Adams
E. Balas
D. Zawack
dcterms:description: ABZ instances are a set of job shop scheduling problems characterized by specific processing times and machine sequences, used to evaluate scheduling algorithms.
dcterms:title: ABZ instances

dcterms:creator: T. Yamada
R. Nakano
dcterms:description: YN instances are a set of job shop scheduling problems designed for testing genetic algorithms, characterized by specific processing times and machine sequences.
dcterms:title: YN instances

dcterms:creator: E. Taillard
dcterms:description: TA instances are benchmark problems for basic scheduling problems, providing a set of job shop scheduling scenarios with varying numbers of machines and jobs.
dcterms:title: TA instances

dcterms:creator: R. H. Storer
S. D. Wu
R. Vaccari
dcterms:description: SWV instances are a set of job shop scheduling problems that introduce new search spaces for sequencing problems, used to evaluate scheduling algorithms.
dcterms:title: SWV instances

dcterms:creator: H. Fisher
dcterms:description: FT instances are a set of job shop scheduling problems used to study probabilistic learning combinations of local scheduling rules.
dcterms:title: FT instances
